Using lambdas you can tidy this up to:
            userState_.get().writeState(boolArg ->
            {
               userPrefs_.get().writeUserPrefs(boolArg1 ->
               {
                     initializeWorkbench();
               });
            });
         }

You could drop the braces and make it more compact, but I personally find that harder to read especially when there are multiple lambda happening at once (but that's just me):
            userState_.get().writeState(boolArg ->
               userPrefs_.get().writeUserPrefs(boolArg1 ->
                  initializeWorkbench()));

